snippet: French investigators’ conclusion partly contradicted and partly confirmed those of Swiss scientists who found abnormal polonium-210 levels in the remains of Yasir Arafat.
abstract: French investigators studying the remains of Yasir Arafat conclude that the Palestinian leader most likely did not die of radiation poisoning.
lead_paragraph: French investigators’ conclusion partly contradicted and partly confirmed those of Swiss scientists who found abnormal polonium-210 levels in the remains of Yasir Arafat.

headline.main: Tests on Arafat Find No Proof of Radiation Poisoning
headline.print_headline: Tests on Arafat Find No Proof Of Poisoning
